==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: blue jeans
<hw>blue" jeans`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>a
tight-fitting trousers made of blue denim or a similar fabric, designed
originally to serve as inexpensive durable workclothes, and often having
metal rivets for reinforcement. They have become very popular as casual
wear for all age groups, and more expensive and more carefully styled
and tailored versions called <ecol><b>designer jeans</b></ecol>have also
become popular among girls and women.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> jeans, Levis.</syn>
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blue-john</ent>⟦br⟧
